		<title>
		Comment on Big News: The Book is Out! by Jennifer		</title>
		<link>http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/10/31/big-news-the-book-is-out/#comment-69</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Jennifer]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 28 Dec 2012 08:05:51 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://gamifyforthewin.com/?p=789#comment-69</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/10/31/big-news-the-book-is-out/#comment-68&quot;&gt;Steve Wallis&lt;/a&gt;.

Steve, 

Thanks for taking an interest in our book and in gamification. We think it&#039;s a great idea to gamify classrooms and likely to be an essential tool to the future of education. 

We wrote an article on the Khan Academy from founder Salman Khan. The article is available here: http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/08/khan-academys-vision-of-the-future-of-education/ 
As you will notice, he has helped implement gamification in several classrooms. 
Info here: http://www.losaltos.k12.ca.us/District/Department/26-Academics/3671-Khan-Academy.html
And here: http://www.khanacademy.org/coach-res/case-studies/v/los-altos

We also wrote on article on a panel titled &quot;Technology in Education: How Will it Change the Game?&quot; Link to the article here (and a link to the panel): http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/07/gaming-as-an-educational-tool/

Those should be some good places to start.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/10/31/big-news-the-book-is-out/#comment-68">Steve Wallis</a>.</p>
<p>Steve, </p>
<p>Thanks for taking an interest in our book and in gamification. We think it&#8217;s a great idea to gamify classrooms and likely to be an essential tool to the future of education. </p>
<p>We wrote an article on the Khan Academy from founder Salman Khan. The article is available here: <a href="http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/08/khan-academys-vision-of-the-future-of-education/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/08/khan-academys-vision-of-the-future-of-education/</a><br />
As you will notice, he has helped implement gamification in several classrooms.<br />
Info here: <a href="http://www.losaltos.k12.ca.us/District/Department/26-Academics/3671-Khan-Academy.html" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.losaltos.k12.ca.us/District/Department/26-Academics/3671-Khan-Academy.html</a><br />
And here: <a href="http://www.khanacademy.org/coach-res/case-studies/v/los-altos" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.khanacademy.org/coach-res/case-studies/v/los-altos</a></p>
<p>We also wrote on article on a panel titled &#8220;Technology in Education: How Will it Change the Game?&#8221; Link to the article here (and a link to the panel): <a href="http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/07/gaming-as-an-educational-tool/" rel="nofollow ugc">http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/07/gaming-as-an-educational-tool/</a></p>
<p>Those should be some good places to start.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>
		Comment on Big News: The Book is Out! by Steve Wallis		</title>
		<link>http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/10/31/big-news-the-book-is-out/#comment-68</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Steve Wallis]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Fri, 28 Dec 2012 07:46:07 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://gamifyforthewin.com/?p=789#comment-68</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[I&#039;m a high school principal reading this as a potential summer reading book for our teaching staff. I see a lot of possibility in learning to use gamification to improve instructional design and practice, and am wondering if you know of any people, schools, or resources I could connect to in order to help me see if this would be a worthwhile direction.

Thanks,
Steve Wallis]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;m a high school principal reading this as a potential summer reading book for our teaching staff. I see a lot of possibility in learning to use gamification to improve instructional design and practice, and am wondering if you know of any people, schools, or resources I could connect to in order to help me see if this would be a worthwhile direction.</p>
<p>Thanks,<br />
Steve Wallis</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
			</item>
		<item>
		<title>
		Comment on Begging, Giving, and Gamification by Tiago		</title>
		<link>http://gamifyforthewin.com/2012/10/16/begging-giving-and-gamification/#comment-66</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Tiago]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Mon, 03 Dec 2012 20:12:10 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://gamifyforthewin.com/?p=760#comment-66</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[As mentioned in previous comments, I don&#039;t think leveling up and earning money would fit to raise awareness on that matter. The gamer wouldn&#039;t feel cold and would leave his character sleeping outside while he has the comfort of his bed, for instance.
Game? Good.
Awareness? Bad.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>As mentioned in previous comments, I don&#8217;t think leveling up and earning money would fit to raise awareness on that matter. The gamer wouldn&#8217;t feel cold and would leave his character sleeping outside while he has the comfort of his bed, for instance.<br />
Game? Good.<br />
Awareness? Bad.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
		
			</item>
